{"id":"2107.11916","submitter":"Anna Torstensson","authors":"Rode Gr\\\"onkvist, Erik Leffler, Anna Torstensson, Victor Ufnarovski","title":"Describing subalgebras of $\\mathbb{K}[x]$ using derivatives","comments":"162 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.RA","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  We introduce the concept of subalgebra spectrum, $Sp(A)$, for a subalgebra\n$A$ of finite codimension in $\\mathbb{K}[x]$. The spectrum is a subset of the\nunderlying field. We also introduce a tool, the characteristic polynomial of\n$A$, which has the spectrum as its set of zeroes. The characteristic polynomial\ncan be computed from the generators of $A$, thus allowing us to find the\nspectrum of an algebra given by generators. We proceed by using the spectrum to\nget descriptions of subalgebras of finite codimension. More precisely we show\nthat $A$ can be described by a set of conditions that each is either of the\ntype $f(\\alpha)=f(\\beta)$ for $\\alpha,\\beta$ in $Sp(A)$ or of the type stating\nthat some sum of derivatives of different orders evaluated in elements of\n$Sp(A)$ equals zero. We use this type of conditions to, by an inductive\nprocess, find explicit descriptions of subalgebras of codimension up to three.\nThese descriptions also include SAGBI bases for each family of subalgebras.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Jul 2021 00:39:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-27"}
